<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3541&amp;p=26407#p26407</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3541&amp;p=26407#p26407"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Portamento Help?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3541&amp;p=26407#p26407"><![CDATA[
The following applies to NT2, MOD, and XM.<br /><br />On the first row, you start a note:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">G-3 01 ---</div><br />On the next row, you write the note to slide to. The digits in 3xx determine how fast, in NES period units per tick, the slide goes:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">G#3 -- 301</div><br />Keep adding rows of 300 to finish the slide:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">--- -- 300<br />--- -- 300<br />--- -- 300</div><br /><br />S3M and IT work the same way, but you use the Gxx and G00 instead of 3xx and 300.)<br /><br />The slide will start on the first row with a 3xx effect; this cannot be the row where the note starts. To start the slide on the first row, place a 1xx (up) or 2xx (down) effect on the first row, and then follow it with the normal chain of 3xx rows. (In S3M or IT, use Fxx for up or Exx for down.)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sun Aug 19, 2007 3:59 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
